Q.1] What is the difference between compiler and interpreter? Asked at: TCS, Wipro, Infosys
Compiler:
    • Translates the entire program into machine code before execution 
    • Execution is fast after compilation 
    • Errors are shown after compiling the whole code 
    • Example: GCC (used for C++) 
Interpreter:
    • Translates and executes code line by line 
    • Execution is slower 
    • Errors are shown immediately, line by line 
Key Difference:
Compiler -> whole program first, then execution
Interpreter -> line-by-line execution immediately
Note:
C++ is a compiled language, so it uses a compiler.


